==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermostat
<hw>Ther"mo*stat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ to make to stand.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A device which automatically regulates
temperature, or provides a signal used by another device to regulate
temperature. The temperature-sensitive signal may be electronic, as that
produced by a thermocouple. The signal may also be caused mechanically,
as by the unequal expansion of different metals, liquids, or gases by
heat, which can then cause the opening or closing of the damper of a
stove, or the like, as the heat becomes greater or less than is
desired.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermostatic</ent>⟦br⟧
